1 Statistics of Read
********************

This chapter presents the _reads statistics_ task of bio-tk.  The
following options are relevant to this task

   * --read, -r indicates the file containing the reads.

   * --outuput-dir, -d indicates the directory where the output will be
     written.

   * --file-name-prefix,-X will use the supplied string as prefix to
     every file name produced.

     To produce all statistics for the file _~/data/in.fastq_ and output in the
     _~/data/out_dir/_ directory with all files having the format
     _experiment001_*_ use the command
       bio-tk readstats
           -r ~/data/in.fastq
           -d ~/data/out_dir
           -X experiment001_

1.1 Statistics produced
=======================

The _reads statistics_ task currently computes the following statistcs.
   * _length_ calculate the distribution of lengths of all reads.
     Results are saved in _prefix_len.btk file.

